    <AppConfig>isoMicro.exe.config</AppConfig>
    <!-- Visual Studio's MS Build copies the isoMicro's "app.config" file into the isoMicro's executable folder as file "isoMicro.exe.config".
				 - Under normal circumstances, directly editing "isoMicro.exe.config" file is highly unadvisable, but for narrow/niche circumstances may prove useful, hence is assisted.
           - Directly editing "isoMicro.exe.config" allows temporary runtime execution changes, but they'll be overwritten the next time MS Build is executed.
           - Changes to "isoMicro.exe.config" also won't be incorporated into the source program's "app.config" file, and are permanently lost the next time MS Build is executed.
           - For the niche case when it's useful to temporarily experiment with isoMicro.exe.config's behavior, and a C# compiler and/or 
             isoMicro source code are unavailable on the isoMicro tester's PC, directly editing isoMicro.exe.config may prove useful.
           - Be sure to backport any permanently desired isoMicro.exe.config changes to file app.config, then re-compile/re-deploy the resulting executable.
           - Also be sure to undo any undesired temporary isoMicro.exe.config changes after experimention is completed.
    -->
    <TestExecutiveConfigXML>TestExecutive.config.xml</TestExecutiveConfigXML>
